external_knowledge:
- 'Golden geese' refers to high-revenue items, implying items that generate significant income; 
- 'running out of eggs' means low in stock; 
- High revenue is defined as total revenue > $10,000; 
- Low stock is defined as quantity_in_stock <= 50.

sql:
SELECT SUM(total_price) AS total_cost_of_pending_orders
FROM order_info
WHERE status = 'pending';

SELECT total_price
FROM order_info
WHERE order_id = 1;
